Package services.xml.exception

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ParserBoundedNodesNumberException
    This type of exception is thrown when the number of nodes of one type is wrong and the expected number is bounded.
    ParserDuplicateObjectException
    This type of exception is thrown when two identical objects are in the xml file, whereas they should be unique.
    ParserException
    This class described a generic exception thrown during the parsing of xml files.
    ParserIntegerValueException
    This type of exception is thrown when an integer value is out of its bounds.
    ParserInvalidIdException
    This type of exception represents an invalid id during parsing, for example a streetSection's id which is not in the previously parse intersections.
    ParserLowerBoundedNodesNumberException
    This type of exception is thrown when the number of nodes of one type is wrong and the expected number is lower bounded.
    ParserMalformedXmlException
    This type of exception is thrown when the file given to the parser is a malformed xml file.
    ParserMissingAttributeException
    This type of exception is thrown when an attribute is missing in the xml file.
    ParserNodesNumberException
    This type of exception is thrown when the number of nodes of one type is invalid.
    ParserSemanticException
    This type of exception is thrown when a semantic error happened while parsing a xml file.
    ParserShouldBeIntegerValueException
    This type of exception is thrown when an attribute in the xml file should be an integer, but is another value.
    ParserSyntaxException
    This type of exception is thrown when a syntax error happened while parsing a xml file.
    ParserTimeConstraintsException
    This type of exception is thrown when the time constraints in a delivery address is invalid.
    ParserTimeSyntaxException
    This type of exception is thrown when a time in the xml file has not the correct syntax.
